Package: spotmapr
Title: Interactive Epidemiological Spot Maps for India
Version: 0.1.11
Authors@R: person("Tharun", "Mallesan", email = "tharunmallesan@gmail.com",
                   role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Build interactive spot maps for epidemiological case-control data
    in India. Supports automatic detection of latitude, longitude, and outcome
    columns, spatial joining with bundled state and district boundaries, and
    produces interactive HTML maps with dot-density and spot-pin display modes.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/ADARV-Epi-hub/spotmapr
BugReports: https://github.com/ADARV-Epi-hub/spotmapr/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    sf,
    leaflet,
    htmltools,
    htmlwidgets,
    readr,
    readxl,
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Config/testthat/edition: 3
LazyData: true
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
